                        <h4>Do I require to remain fasting? </h4> <div class="spend-btn"> </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accrodion-content"> 
                        <div class="content-box"> 
                            <p>If your health care provider has told you to fast before a blood test, it means you should not eat or drink anything, except water, for 8-10 hours prior to your test. When you eat and drink normally, those foods and beverages are absorbed into your bloodstream. That could affect the results of certain types of blood tests. </p>
                            <p>Ideal time required for fasting Blood Glucose, Hormones and other blood parameters is 8-10 hours. Lipid profile 12-14 hours. </p> 
